{"name": "pytest-embedded-wokwi", "metadata": {"name": "pytest-embedded-wokwi", "version": "1.12.1", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 5 - Production/Stable", "Framework :: Pytest", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3 :: Only", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.13", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9", "Topic :: Software Development :: Testing"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["pytest-embedded", "toml"], "summary": "Make pytest-embedded plugin work with the Wokwi CLI.", "upload_time": 1733127010}, "documentation": ["### pytest-embedded-wokwi\n\npytest-embedded service for running tests on [Wokwi](https://wokwi.com/ci) instead of the real target.\n\nWokwi supports most ESP32 targets, including: esp32, esp32s2, esp32s3, esp32c3, esp32c6, and esp32h2. In addition, it supports a [wide range of peripherals](https://docs.wokwi.com/getting-started/supported-hardware), including sensors, displays, motors, and debugging tools.\n\nRunning the tests with Wokwi requires an internet connection. Your firmware is uploaded to the Wokwi server for the duration of the simulation, but it is not saved on the server. On-premises Wokwi installations are available for enterprise customers.\n\n#### Wokwi CLI installation\n\nThe Wokwi plugin uses the [Wokwi CLI](https://github.com/wokwi/wokwi-cli) to interact with the wokwi simulation server. You can download the precompiled CLI binaries from the [releases page](https://github.com/wokwi/wokwi-cli/releases). Alternatively, on Linux or Mac OS, you can install the CLI using the following command:\n\n```bash\ncurl -L https://wokwi.com/ci/install.sh | sh\n```\n\nAnd on Windows:\n\n```powershell\niwr https://wokwi.com/ci/install.ps1 -useb | iex\n```\n\n#### Wokwi API Tokens\n\nBefore using this plugin, you need to create a free Wokwi account and [generate an API key](https://wokwi.com/dashboard/ci). You can then set the `WOKWI_CLI_TOKEN` environment variable to the API key.\n\nLinux / Mac OS / WSL:\n\n```bash\nexport WOKWI_CLI_TOKEN=\"your-api-key\"\n```\n\nWindows PowerShell:\n\n```powershell\n$env:WOKWI_CLI_TOKEN=\"your-api-key\"\n```\n\n#### Usage\n\nTo run your tests with Wokwi, make sure to specify the `wokwi` service when running pytest, e.g.:\n\n```\npytest --embedded-services idf,wokwi\n```\n\nTo limit the amount of simulation time, use the `--wokwi-timeout` flag. For example, to set the simulation time limit to 60 seconds (60000 milliseconds):\n\n```\npytest --embedded-services idf,wokwi --wokwi-timeout=60000\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "pytest_embedded_wokwi.idf", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "pytest_embedded_wokwi.idf.IDFFirmwareResolver", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "pytest_embedded_wokwi.idf.IDFFirmwareResolver.resolve_firmware", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "app", "type": {"name": "IdfApp", "xref": {"fqname": "pytest_embedded_idf.app.IdfApp", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["IDFFirmwareResolver class"]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "pytest_embedded_wokwi", "documentation": ["Make pytest-embedded plugin work with the Wokwi CLI."], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "pytest_embedded_wokwi.WOKWI_CLI_MINIMUM_VERSION", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pytest_embedded_wokwi.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "pytest_embedded_wokwi.WOKWI_CLI_MINIMUM_VERSION", "xref": {"fqname": "pytest_embedded_wokwi.WOKWI_CLI_MINIMUM_VERSION", "project": null}}, {"name": "pytest_embedded_wokwi.WokwiCLI", "xref": {"fqname": "pytest_embedded_wokwi.wokwi_cli.WokwiCLI", "project": null}}, {"name": "pytest_embedded_wokwi.WokwiDut", "xref": {"fqname": "pytest_embedded_wokwi.dut.WokwiDut", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "pytest_embedded_wokwi.dut", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "pytest_embedded_wokwi.dut.WokwiDut", "bases": ["Dut"], "methods": [{"name": "pytest_embedded_wokwi.dut.WokwiDut.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "wokwi", "type": {"name": "WokwiCLI", "xref": {"fqname": "pytest_embedded_wokwi.dut.wokwi_cli.WokwiCLI", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pytest_embedded_wokwi.dut.WokwiDut.write", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "s", "type": {"name": "AnyStr", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.AnyStr", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Wokwi DUT class"]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "pytest_embedded_wokwi.arduino", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "pytest_embedded_wokwi.arduino.ArduinoFirmwareResolver", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "pytest_embedded_wokwi.arduino.ArduinoFirmwareResolver.resolve_firmware", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "app", "type": {"name": "ArduinoApp", "xref": {"fqname"